doc.previous: Another futhorc row is found in Cotton Galba A ii
doc.after: The 9th century Codex Sangallensis 878 attributed to Walahfrid Strabo records an abecedarium anguliscum in three lines The first two lines list the standard 29 runes i e the 24 derived from Elder Futhark and the five standard additional ones io ea The listing order of the final two of the elder 24 runes is d g el A peculiarity is the asterisk shape of eolh The third line lists gar and kalc before a doodling repetition of other runes
